Preheat your oven to 200°C and put your #kettle on to boil. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and pepper, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until the chicken is browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally. Meanwhile, put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Pour in the @water{75%ml} and add the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1/2%tin} into the pan with the chicken. Stir in the @tomato puree{30%g}, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium until the sauce is simmering away. Cook until the sauce has thickened and the veggies are soft, stirring occasionally, about ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. When the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan. Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add half the parsley to the chicken and veggies and stir through. Transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the creamy pasta. Cover with the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and pop on the top shelf of your oven. Bake until the top is golden and a little crunchy at the edges, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Serve the chicken pasta bake in #bowls{} and finish with a sprinkling of the remaining parsley. Enjoy!

> Step 2 MOD: If you've chosen to get chicken breast instead of chicken thigh, cook the recipe in the same way the instructions tell you to cook the chicken thigh.